<isis lang="en">
    <stitle>ALTERNATOR: DELCO-REMY 26-SI SERIES - REPAIR PROCEDURES - DIODE TRIO CHECK</stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="check" graphiccount="1">
        <title>DIODE TRIO CHECK</title>
        <para>To check the diode trio, connect the NEG (-) lead of an ohmmeter using the lower scale (Rx1 or Rx10) to
            the field regulator connector lead (F+) (
            <hotlnk xrefid="f0801809">Figure 8</hotlnk>) on the diode trio and the POS(+) lead of the ohmmeter on each
            of the three rectifier bridge terminal lead connectors on the diode trio. The readings should show
            continuity. The ohmmeter should show an open from F+ to the three rectifier bridge terminal connectors when
            the leads are reversed. If any of the six tests are not as described, the diode trio is bad and must be
            replaced.
        </para>
        <figure id="f0801809" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic id="g0801808" filename="../figg08/G0801808.webp" type="webp"/>
            <caption>Diode Trio Check</caption>
            <calloutgroup>
                <callout1>1. "R" TERMINAL CONNECTOR</callout1>
                <callout1>2. CAPACITOR GROUND AND MOUNTING TAB</callout1>
                <callout1>3. FIELD REGULATOR LEAD CONNECTOR (F+)</callout1>
                <callout1>4. OHMMETER</callout1>
                <callout1>5. RECTIFIER BRIDGE TERMINAL LEAD CONNECTOR</callout1>
                <callout1>6. CAPACITOR LEAD CONNECTOR</callout1>
                <callout1>7. RECTIFIER BRIDGE TERMINAL LEAD CONNECTOR</callout1>
                <callout1>8. RECTIFIER BRIDGE TERMINAL LEAD CONNECTOR</callout1>
                <callout1>9. DIODE TRIO CAPACITOR ASSEMBLY</callout1>
            </calloutgroup>
        </figure>
    </svcproc>
